Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Peel @plantain{1}, 
then slice into ½-inch-thick rounds. Drain and rinse @black beans{1%box}, 
reserving ¼ cup liquid from can. Thinly slice @radishes{3}. Halve, peel, 
and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Halve, pit, and peel @avocado{1}, then thinly 
slice. Halve @lime{1}. Cut one half into wedges.

In a #small bowl{}, toss a quarter of the onion with juice from lime half.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. 
Add remaining onion and cook, tossing, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add beans 
and @cumin{1%teaspoon} and stir until warm, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat. 
Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until creamy, adding reserved bean 
liquid as needed to reduce stiffness. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place @flour tortillas{4} on a #baking sheet{}. Toast in oven until golden 
brown and crisp, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Remove bean mixture from pan and cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan, then heat 
a thin layer of oil in it (we used 1 TBSP) over medium-high heat. Add plantain 
and cook until soft and browned, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Reduce heat if plantain browns before soft.

Remove from pan, then drizzle with @honey{1%teaspoon}. Season with salt and 
pepper.

Top tortillas with bean mixture, plantain, avocado, pickled onion, radishes, 
and a few sprigs of @cilantro{¼%ounce}. Sprinkle with @feta cheese{½%cup} and 
squeeze over a bit of lime. Serve with lime wedges on the side for squeezing 
over.